<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-1269] AsyncLogger should use thread-local translator by default</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-1269</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Bug in the fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-1172&quot; title=&quot;ThreadLocal leak [AsyncLogger$Info] on Tomcat when using AsyncLoggerContextSelector&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LOG4J2-1172&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LOG4J2-1172&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
The current default is to use a vararg translator. This was intended to only be used in web containers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix is to change &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//AsyncLoggerDisruptor
&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;boolean&lt;/span&gt; useThreadLocalTranslator;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;to&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;boolean&lt;/span&gt; useThreadLocalTranslator = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
